HEADWORD: Provisory
<hw>Pro*vi"so*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>provisoire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of the nature of a
proviso; containing a proviso or condition; conditional; <as>as, a
<ex>provisory</ex> clause</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Making temporary provision; provisional.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provocation</ent>⟦br⟧
